## 1\. TrustMesh Origins: Built in the Fire of Compliance

TrustMesh wasnâ€™t born out of a whitepaperâ€”it was forged in one of the most complex regulated industries in the world: cannabis finance.

Under a grant to build decentralized infrastructure for the cannabis sector, we didnâ€™t start with theoriesâ€”we started with regulators, custody, and compliance audits. The space demanded **verifiable identity, immutable logs, and real-time audits**â€”requirements that make most Web3 projects fold. But we saw an opportunity:

If we could build programmable trust for cannabis, we could build it for any industry.

Thatâ€™s where TrustMesh began: not as a social network, but as a compliance-first infrastructure for authentic, sovereign digital trust.

Now, under the pressure and visibility of the Hedera Hackathon, the broader architecture and civic potential of TrustMesh is coming into full viewâ€”transforming from a specialized compliance tool into a general-purpose framework for decentralized trust infrastructure.

