## 3\. Live Standards in Action

TrustMesh is powered entirely by Hedera-native HCS standards. No custom middleware. No walled gardens. Just composable, interoperable protocols:

| HCS Standard | Role in TrustMesh | Outcome |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **HCS-11** â€“ Profile Metadata | Defines portable identity and trust graph anchors | Self-sovereign, app-independent reputation |
| **HCS-5** â€“ Hashinals (Static NFTs) | Anchors immutable trust signals | Cross-platform recognition and proof |
| **HCS-2** â€“ Topic Registries | Categorizes signal types and domains | Scalable trust circle taxonomy |
| **HCS-3** â€“ Recursive References | Trust nodes can reference others | Enables nested, lineage-aware trust |
| **HCS-8/9** â€“ Poll Topics | Civic and governance primitives | Verified trust-based voting mechanisms |

These are live. Not theoretical. All acknowledgment, voting, and relational data in our hackathon demo is standards-native and deployable now.

